06171nam a22007215i 9783866539655DE-B159720211129102213.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211129t20122012gw     fo  d z      eng d  a(OCoLC)840437912  a97838665396557 a10.1515/97838665396552doi  a(DE-B1597)206419  a(OCoLC)820556675  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAW0000002bisacsh04a34000aCoherence and Fragmentation in European Private Law /ced. by Pia Letto-Vanamo, Jan Smits. 1aMunich : bOtto Schmidt/De Gruyter european law publishers, c[2012] 4c©2012  a1 online resource (172 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- tCoherence and Fragmentation in the Law of Contract -- tQuasi-coherence by Harmonisation of EU Competition Law-related Damages Actions? -- tLegal Coherence as a Prerequisite for a Single European Insurance Market -- tAccommodating Intellectual Property in Competition Policy: Approaches for Advancing the Shared Goal of Innovation -- tFrom Coherent to Fragmented and Europeanized Nordic Marketing Law -- tCoherence through Uniform Private International Law of Property -- tCollision Between the Economic and the Social – What Has Private International Law Got to Do with It? -- tFragmentation and Coherence of Law – a Historical Approach -- tBackmatter0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDie Vorbereitungen laufen bereits viele Jahre, nun liegt er endlich vor: der Entwurf der Europäischen Kommission für ein Gemeinsames Europäisches Kaufrecht als Optionales Instrument. Beteiligte an den Vorarbeiten und wichtige Kritiker derselben setzen sich in diesem höchst empfehlenswerten Buch mit dem Kommissionsentwurf auseinander. Wie wird die Harmonisierung des europäischen Vertragsrechts durch den Entwurf vorangetrieben? Wie "schlägt" sich der Entwurf im Vergleich zum BGB, zum DCFR oder zu den Acquis-Principles? Beleuchtet werden insbesondere Irrtumsanfechtung, AGB-Kontrolle, allgemeines und besonderes Leistungsstörungsrecht beim Kauf und bei verbundenen Dienstleistungen sowie übergreifende Fragestellungen zum Verbraucherrecht. Der Band wird abgerundet durch eine Synopse des Kommissionsentwurfs und der vorangegangenen Machbarkeitsstudie, in der die Entwicklung des Textes deutlich wird.  aOne of the most important characteristics of today’s private law is that it increasingly flows from different sources: Next to national legislation and case law, it is also shaped by European and supranational sources and rapidly becoming a mixture of differently oriented rules and principles. This development can be described as one from coherence to fragmentation. The aim of the new book is to consider how this important shift has worked out in different subfields of the law like in contract and property law, in competition, insurance, marketing and private international law as well as in the law of intellectual property. This cross-disciplinary approach shows how pervasive legal fragmentation has become, and points out how to remedy the adverse effects it brings with it. The volume is therefore indispensable for anyone interested in how Europeanisation affects national private laws.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh1 aBärlund, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHavu, Katri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJuutilainen, Teemu, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLetto-Vanamo, Pia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLetto-Vanamo, Pia, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLiukkunen, Ulla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/